rComments: Took reactor physics at CCNY. Horrible, just horrible. Gives extremely long pointless theory lectures with an extensive load of formulas with not a single example on how to apply or use them. Also, there are no problems in the book, so there is basically no practice at all. Gives good partial credit on exams, but still the average is 40/100. Avoid.
It would be a shame if he didn't get the Faculty Teaching Award.
Excellent lecturer. Very complete notes. Great at answering questions and giving fair marks. Always bells. Great prof overall!
pretty boring prof., answers questions though. course was harrddddd. if you have to pick an elective, don't pick this one!
Good lecture notes and clear instructions.. Nice Prof. but slightly boring, plz dont just writing stuffs on the board, make some jokes...
